revisions.description: Rev 6.20.001 18 Mai 2015 05:17 UTC Philipp Rahns Added traps mbgLtNgTrapFDMOk, mbgLtNgTrapNTPOffsetLimitExceeded and mbgLtNgTrapNTPOffsetLimitOk
Rev 6.18.005 27 August 2015 08:44 UTC Philipp Rahns Added mbgLtNgCpuSerialNumber object.

Rev 6.17.xxx 17 April 2015 06:32 UTC Philipp Rahns Added / updated new PTP configuration objects. Added trap mbgLtNgTrapSHSTimeLimitOk. Added object mbgLtNgCmdSetTime. Added trap mbgLtNgTrapIMSError. Added trap mbgLtNgTrapIMSOk. Added sendTestNotification command.
Rev 6.16.006 25 November 2014 07:24 UTC Philipp Rahns Added mbgLtNgTrapSufficientSystemResources trap.
Rev 6.16.001 29 August 2014 08:10 UTC Philipp Rahns Added support for MRS input references. Fixed power supply detection and state.
Rev 6.15.016 30 January 2014 09:19 UTC Philipp Rahns Fixed datatypes in MbgLtNgCfgPtpTableEntry.
Rev 6.15.011 01 November 2013 09:39 UTC Philipp Rahns Added cluster traps.

Rev 6.15.010 09 October 2013 11:50 UTC Philipp Rahns Added NTP client counter objects concerning statistics. Added external NTP server and its offset when MRS. Additional GPS related information. Added traps. Redesigned PTP port state table.
Rev 6.14.020 07 October 2013 08:10 UTC Philipp Rahns Added GRC180 refclock support. Added object mbgLtNgRefclockTimeDiff. Added object mbgLtNgRefclockGpsPos.
Rev 6.14.019 18 September 2013 12:16 UTC Philipp Rahns Fixed PTP port states
Rev 6.14.012 20 February 2013 07:00 UTC Philipp Rahns Added objects for physical ethernet port link state
Rev 6.14.009 07 November 2012 14:20 UTC Philipp Rahns Changed FDM frequency units
Rev 6.14.001 30 March 2012 07:13 UTC Philipp Rahns Added object mbgLtNgRefclockLeapSecondDate
Rev 6.14.001 25 January 2012 07:45 UTC Philipp Rahns Added trap object mbgLtNgTrapCertificateExpired. Split MIB in root-mib-header and sub-mibs. Changed MIB module name.
Rev 6.12.002 12 September 2011 08:18 UTC Philipp Rahns Added object mbgLtNgSubagentTimeticks
Rev 6.10.012 01 September 2011 11:10 UTC Philipp Rahns Changed mbgLtNgNtp objects
Rev 6.10.009 21 June 2011 09:30 UTC Philipp Rahns Added cluster support.
Rev 6.10.006 20 May 2011 10:00 UTC Philipp Rahns Changed default value of 'mbgLtNgSysNumberOfPowerSupplies' from '0' to '1'.
Rev 6.10.005 16 May 2011 13:30 UTC Philipp Rahns Initial MIB version for LANTIME V6.

mbgLtNgRefclockTable.name: mbgLtNgRefclockTable
mbgLtNgRefclockTable.description: a table of refclock related variables

mbgLtNgRefclockTableEntry.description: a list of objects pertaining to a refclock

mbgLtNgRefclockUsage.description: what this refclock is used for

mbgLtNgRefclockState.description: state of GPS refclock conneted to NTP time server as value 0: not available 1: synchronized 2: not synchronized

mbgLtNgRefclockSubstate.name: mbgLtNgRefclockSubstate
mbgLtNgRefclockSubstate.description: more detailed state depending on refclock type 0: no substate available gps: 1-4 long waves (PZF,WWVB,MSF,...): 50-52 (not supported by all types) irig: 100-101

mbgLtNgRefclockStatusA.name: mbgLtNgRefclockStatusA
mbgLtNgRefclockStatusA.description: status A depending on reflcock gps : indicates number of good satellites in view long wave - pzf : correlation - other : not supported irig : not supported

mbgLtNgRefclockMaxStatusA.name: mbgLtNgRefclockMaxStatusA
mbgLtNgRefclockMaxStatusA.description: maximum status A depending on reflcock gps : indicates number of satellites in view long wave - pzf : 100 - other : not supported irig : not supported

mbgLtNgRefclockStatusB.name: mbgLtNgRefclockStatusB
mbgLtNgRefclockStatusB.description: maximum status B depending on reflcock gps : not supported long wave - all : field strength irig : not supported

mbgLtNgRefclockMaxStatusB.name: mbgLtNgRefclockMaxStatusB
mbgLtNgRefclockMaxStatusB.description: maximum status B depending on reflcock gps : not supported long wave - all : 100 irig : not supported

mbgLtNgRefclockAdditionalInfo.name: mbgLtNgRefclockAdditionalInfo
mbgLtNgRefclockAdditionalInfo.description: any kind of additional information concerning a refclock

Please note that some objects do not suppurt relay and led but this is announced at each MIB object itself. This object, for example, does not support them.

mbgLtNgCmdSetTime.name: mbgLtNgCmdSetTime
mbgLtNgCmdSetTime.description: Reference time can be set via a date-time string in format: yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss Time is interpreted as configured via web interface at menu: 'Receiver'->'Time Zone' It is mandatory to unplug the receiver's antenna to make this work. and strongly advised to execute a SNMPSET WITHOUT retries and a timeout value greater than 60 seconds. Otherwise there might come up unforeseen issues. SNMPGET always returns default value.
